    subject: "Please Review and Acknowledge the i58 Deutschland Driver Policy",
    body: "Dear    {{firstName}}    , \n   I hope you're doing well! \n \n\n   Below, you'll find the driver policy for i58 Deutschland. When you have a moment, please read through it carefully. Once you've reviewed the policy, kindly click the \"Agree\" button at the bottom to confirm your acknowledgment. \n \n\n     Please be sure to complete this before arriving in Germany.   \n \n\n   Thank you for your attention and cooperation! If you have any questions, feel free to reach out. \n \n\n \n\n   i58 Deutschland Vehicle Usage Policy  \n\n     Introduction:   \n \n\n   This policy outlines the terms and conditions for individuals driving vehicles owned by i58 Deutschland, hereinafter referred to as \"i58.\" The use of i58 vehicles is primarily intended for volunteer teams working with i58. It is essential to understand and complywith the following rules and responsibilities when operating an i58 vehicle. \n \n\n     1. Eligibility and Requirements:   \n \n\n     1.1 Age and License:      To drive an i58 vehicle, you must be at least 18 years old and \n   possess a valid driver's license. \n     1.2 Legal Compliance:      You must adhere to all German driving laws, including speed \n   limits, road signs, and driving etiquette. Compliance with passenger laws, such as seat \n   belt usage, is also mandatory. \n \n\n     2. Vehicle Use and Responsibility:   \n \n\n     2.1          Accidents and Repairs:      When driving an i58 vehicle, you assume full responsibility \n   for accidents and repairs resulting from user error. Normal wear and tear and \n   maintenance are provided by i58. \n     2.2          Damage Liability:      If you cause scratches or dents on the vehicle, you are \n   responsible for repair costs. Specifically: \n   For each scratch per panel that ruins the paint: €100. \n   For each dent per panel (minor dents): €150. \n   (if both a scratch and dent are made, it is still €150) \n   Major dents and scratches will be evaluated individually. \n   i58 reserves the right to charge additional fees for unusual or extensive damage. \n \n\n     3. Fuel Expenses:   \n \n\n     3.1          Ministry Expenses:      i58 provides fuel for ministry-related expenses. This includes \n   official i58 activities and tasks. \n     3.2          Personal Trips:      If you use an i58 vehicle for personal trips, you are responsible for \n   covering the cost of fuel for those journeys. i58 will not provide fuel reimbursement for \n   personal usage. Personal trips are not guaranteed, and even if the vehicle has been \n   reserved for a personal trip, i58 reserves the right to cancel the reservation if official i58 \n   vehicle use is needed. \n \n\n     4. Tickets and Fines:   \n \n\n     4.1          Traffic Tickets:      You are responsible for any traffic tickets or fines incurred while \n   operating an i58 vehicle. These tickets should be promptly reported to i58. \n     4.2          Additional Expenses:      If your ticket leads to extra expenses for the owner of the \n   vehicle (e.g., increased insurance premiums, legal fees), you will be liable for covering \n   these additional costs. \n \n\n     5. Public Transport Tickets:   \n \n\n     5.1          Usage:      Each volunteer is expected to buy a Germany-wide public transport ticket as \n   our ministry model is somewhat spread out over several locations. These are monthly \n   subscriptions that are not covered in your volunteer pledge due to logistical reasons. \n   We encourage you to use them when possible to reduce the need for vehicles. \n \n\n     6. Acknowledgment and Agreement:   \n \n\n   By agreeing to this policy, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agreed to \n   comply with the terms and conditions outlined herein. You further acknowledge that you \n   will adhere to all German driving laws, take responsibility for damage incurred while \n   operating the vehicle, and cover any traffic tickets and associated expenses. \n   Effective Date: September 2024  \n\n \n\n \n\n \n\n     Click to Agree",
